caption: Sommer early mornings Super fresh, clear sky, fabulous view of Eiffel tower and des Invalides. The garden man working already at 8 am is very kind and friendly.  Couple of guys training too...Birds and fresh air...try!

Paris and Spring means Paradise.  Magic is here to stay. A closer look at places I passed by 100 times and never indulged to discover in detail.  Today “ Square d’Ajaccio “ 1865, Napoleon III.  Super romantic secret corner nearby the Napoleon’s tomb, by Les Invalides with a mixed diversity of century old trees and very lively colored  flowers. Green grass was an invitation to roll onto  its freshness.  Statue: “La Défense du foyer” by Sculptor  Emile Boisseau a strikingly determined husband with his elbow raised, the woman on her knees and the dead child at their feet. It’s a very powerful Sculpture in One piece of rock.  The man’s fierce look of protection, devotion, hate, conquest mixed with the pain shown in his wife’s eyes  Continued a slow walk on and nearby Bridge Alexandre 3, and by the Seine.  Under the bridge this un noticed before alignment of its powerful legs, handicapped my desire to take any further steps for a bit.  I was caught off-guard by so much beauty, by so much architectural opulence, by its exquisitely  cut dimensions. A gorgeous day of history and tons of the best memories.

The most beautiful thing when you visit Paris on a sunny day is wandering the city walking. It is not the most beautiful city by chance! Walk and when your tired have a coffee then wak again and see the beauties of the city
Small but adorable, with a view on the Eiffel Tower !
Beautiful park ( specially at night). Will like it.
It’s a beautiful park with a lovely playground, but gets only three stars because 1. the playground is tiny and 2. currently (07.09.21) closed without any indication as to when it will reopen!
Great place to sit and bring your kids or just to sit in nature for a moment.   Wonderful well kept gardens

Ideal place for a restful while to reach the "vital epticism" of de Unamuno ,bearing in mind the fate of the veterans in the Invalides. To be noted: on the opposite corner The Square Santiago de Chile and Pablo Neruda is not far and Antoine de Saint Expupery also. The scuptor Alphand crowns the whole. Both squares are nesles with seldon and ancient trees.
A cozy and natural place to have a nap after a long walk in the city.
Nice park for a quick break from the sun.
Beautiful but very busy with people
Beautiful garden in Paris
Nice spot to take a break as your are making your wag through Paris.
Nice view
Beautiful place!
beautiful!
Nice little park on the left side of Les Invalids. You can see the archery events there!
Very beautiful park with a superb view of the Eiffel Tower. Near Les Invalides but with all the calm and nature that is missing there.
Very pretty park, located on the Invalides side with a beautiful view of the Eiffel Tower. There are lots of benches and games for children.
Quiet and shaded place with a view of the Eiffel Tower ✨

A small French garden, with flowers and suggestive views where you can glimpse the Eiffel Tower, although it is a small strip of green next to the weapons museum it is a small jewel, well-kept and clean. Perfect for a quick lunch break.

Beautiful park well hidden in Paris with beautiful views of the city and the Eiffel Tower. It is located in a privileged location in the capital between the National Museum of Invalides and the Rodin Museum. I recommend visiting for photos or a casual afternoon stroll.
Small square a stone's throw from Les Invalides and the Ministry of Labor. Well maintained, quiet, allows you to take a quick lunch break.
Nice green area, ideal for a little break. You can even come across a wren among the pigeons.
A small park, very comfortable for a morning walk and rest, windy, not hot in summer, very quiet, you can do your own thing by yourself, suitable for meditation
It is a small but forest-like park located between the Rodin Museum and the Military Museum. I can see the Eiffel Tower.

I love this square for a picnic or a break during the day, because it’s very cool under the big trees. Very well maintained and flowery with a magnificent magnolia when it is in flower. 2 beautiful statues A beautiful view of the Eiffel Tower A small play area for children Unfortunately a little noisy, as it overlooks the Boulevard des Invalides. But otherwise, very relaxing.

Very pretty little square, very designed with a delicate statue in the middle and beds of multicolored flowers which wonderfully brighten up the green lawns! Sitting on a bench you have a distant view of the Eiffel Tower and Napoleon's tomb, under this brilliant golden dome... A welcome time for rest and greenery right next to the very interesting Army Museum.
Very pleasant neighborhood, square with breathtaking views. I highly recommend this place.
Superb little clean square (but without trash) with pleasant benches far from each other. A very small children's play area.
The Ajacio square is charming, a pretty garden, some statues and a beautiful view; you can see the Eiffel Tower. Quiet and calm, this square is pleasant. Conducive to pleasure and relaxation.
A stone's throw from Les Invalides, don't miss this Magnolia dating back more than three centuries.
Very nice park and you can see rabbits! It's great!

This discreet little green space - created in 1865, during the reign of Napoleon III - is remarkably well maintained. It houses three works: a sculpted group - La Défense du Foyer (1887) - by Boisseau, a bronze medallion by Roty representing the philosopher and historian Hyppolyte Taine (1928) as well as a statue of General Gouraud (1989), military governor from Paris from 1923 to 1937.
Small park near Les Invalides well maintained benches and games for children statues glimpse of the Eiffel Tower
Nice little park to relax after a long visit.  Very green and calming and clean!
quite quiet close to ministries and embassies View of the Eiffel Tower through the centuries-old trees near Les Invalides well maintained
Cute little park next to Les Invalides. Open all year except in the event of severe storms.
